com.sap.conn.idoc.jco

Interface JCoIDocQueueHandler

  • All Superinterfaces:
    JCoIDocHandler

    public interface JCoIDocQueueHandler
extends JCoIDocHandler
    The JCoIDocQueueHandler should be implemented by an application in order to process incoming IDocs. In contrast to the JCoIDocHandler an application implementing this interface is able to also process IDocs that shall be queued on the IDoc layer. If your application cannot guarantee to handle this correctly, implementing only the JCoIDocHandler interface is the better choice.
    Note: If a JCoIDocQueueHandler is provided, all requests will be passed to it, regardless whether the transferred IDocs should be queued or not.
    Since:
    IDocLibrary 3.0.8

    • Method Detail

      • handleRequest

        void handleRequest(JCoIDocServerContext serverCtx,
                   IDocDocumentList[] idocLists)
        This method should process the passed IDocDocumentList[] in an application specific way. The sequence of received IDocs is always kept in their original order of sending. As long as consecutive IDocs are of the same type and extension, they will be bundled and passed as elements of the same IDocDocumentList object within the array of IDoc document lists.
        Parameters:
        serverCtx - the IDoc server context, from which an application should retrieve the queue name for queued IDocs.
        idocLists - the IDoc document lists to process.
